tail.el is a small interface for the unix tool tail.

You can download it here: http://www.grassouille.org/code/sources/tail.el

The above doesn't work.  Try this: http://inferno.cs.univ-paris8.fr/~drieu/hacks/sources/tail.el

The above link is broken too. Try this: http://www.drieu.org/code/sources/tail.el

== Configuration ==

Put tail.el in your <code>load-path</code> and this in your .emacs file:

 (require 'tail)

Alternatively you can use <code>autoload</code> (replace <code><path></code> with to local path):

 (autoload 'tail-file "<path>/tail.el" "Tail a file." t)
 (autoload 'tail-command "<path>/tail.el" "Tail a file with arguments." t)

== Screenshot ==

Using the <code>tail-file</code> command with /var/log/syslog:

http://www.knittig.de/img/tailel.png


